  "title": "FOOD PRODUCTION TECHNICIAN",
  "description": "<p>A Food Production technician is responsible for preparing and processing foods, ensuring that production meets quality standards and is delivered in a timely manner. Duties include operating small kitchen equitments like Mixer Grinder, Deep Frier, Buy Electric Cookers, packing and monitoring product quality.</p><p>A food production technician is need to prepare and package foods according to the company's standards. Food production workers may also be responsible for maintaining a safe and hygienic working environment, following food safety regulations and ensuring products meet food safety requirements.</p><p>Duties and Responsibilities</p><p>•\tAssist with the preparation of food items</p><p>•\tEnsure the kitchen and production area are kept clean and tidy</p><p>•\tCheck ingredients and food products for quality</p><p>•\tPackage food items ready for sale</p><p>•\tFollow food safety regulations and health codes</p><p>•\tPreparing ingredients for the shift; washing vegetables, chopping, seasoning meat, etc.</p><p>•\tPreparing deep fryer, utensils, and grill for shift</p><p>•\tRoti prate flour mixing</p><p>•\tReady to cook Goring items (nasi,ikanpils,mee,kwithya,noodles)</p><p>•\tpreparation of south indian & north indian curies</p><p>•\tCooking order according to food health and safety standards</p><p>•\tDelivering food order to wait staff in a timely manner</p><p>•\tStoring all food properly</p><p>•\tSanitizing and cleaning work stations and utensils</p><p>•\tReordering stock and food supplies</p><p>•\tMonitoring other cooks and team members</p><p>Requirements and Qualifications</p><p>•\tReady to work any shift</p><p>•\tAble to work in a fast-paced environment</p><p>•\tAble to multitask, prioritize, and manage time efficiently</p><p>•\tPhysical endurance to stand for an entire shift</p><p>•\tSelf-motivated and self-directed</p><p>•\tWorks well as part of a team and on individual tasks</p><p>•\tAble to quickly memorize complex or multiple orders</p><p>•\tDegree or Diploma or minimum three years relevant work experience</p><p>•\tAble to work early mornings, nights, and weekends</p><p></p>",
